Object.Field: LKM SQL to Sybase IQ (LOAD TABLE)

COMPONENT NAME: LKM SQL to Sybase IQ (LOAD TABLE)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ISO-92 to a Sybase IQ database using Load Table statement. - This module uses ODI Command SnpsSqlUnload to extract data in a temporary file. Data is loaded in the target temporary Sybase IQ table created dynamically using the LOAD TABLE Sybase IQ SQL statement. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
Restrictions: - The option DEFAULT_DIRECTORY indicates the location of the temporary generated file. It must be accessible by both ODI Agent and the Sybase IQ instance.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Temp. Directory for the data file

Directory where the temporary data file is created. This directory must be a valid path on the machine running the ODI Agent. Examples: - On Windows: D:\MyDatafiles\MyTemporaryFolder - On Unix / Linux: /usr/tmp
The maximum amount of memory (in MB) that Sybase IQ will use to load the file.

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

LOAD TABLE <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]", " '~',\n\t", " '\\x0D'","")%> ) FROM '<%=odiRef.getOption("DEFAULT_DIRECTORY")%>/<%=odiRef.getInfo("COLL_NAME")%>.dmp' QUOTES OFF ESCAPES OFF FORMAT ascii ROW DELIMITED BY '\x0A'

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
